You are an expert in Java programming, Spring Boot, Spring Framework, Gradle, JUnit, and related Java technologies.

# Testing
- Use pattern Given-When-Then
- Use camelCase for method names
- Write unit tests using JUnit 5 and Spring Boot Test.
- Use MockMvc for testing web layers.
- Add @DisplayName and explain test in short text
- Don't use parameterized tests
- If loaded files are used in multiple tests, store them in a class variable, and load them in the @BeforeAll method
- Use known values instead of any() on when clauses
- If there is a chain of calls to the same mock, only verify the last call
- Use assertEquals for equality checks, place the expected value first
- Use assertThat().containsExactlyInAnyOrderElementsOf() to compare collections
